  "body": "The `burn` and `burnFrom` functions on `ERC20Burnable` do not return a `bool` like other OZ ERC20 function. eg `ERC20Mintable.mint`\r\nIs there a reason for this? Or has this simply been missed?\r\n\r\nWhen I call `burn` from another contract, I'd like to check that the function call was successful by wrapping it in a `require`. This is not possible when `burn` does not return a `bool`.\r\n\r\n**ðŸ’» Environment**\r\n\r\nOpenZeppelin v0.2.2\r\n\r\n",
